          "title": "Site-to-Site VPN settings",
          "helpText": "AWS Site-to-Site VPN extends your data center or branch office to the cloud via IP Security (IPSec) tunnels, and supports connecting to both virtual private gateway and AWS Transit Gateway. If you choose to create an AWS Site-to-Site VPN connection to your Amazon VPC, you are charged for each VPN connection-hour that your VPN connection is provisioned and available. Each partial VPN connection-hour consumed is billed as a full hour. You also incur standard AWS data transfer charges for all data transferred via the VPN connection.",
